Here’s the general rule and then the special cases for a 5th‐order tensor.

1.  General \( (p,q)\)–tensor under the change of coordinates \(x^i\to x'^{\,i}\):  
   \[
     T'{}^{\,i'_1\cdots i'_p}{}_{\,j'_1\cdots j'_q}
     =\Bigl(\frac{\partial x'^{\,i'_1}}{\partial x^{a_1}}\Bigr)\cdots
      \Bigl(\frac{\partial x'^{\,i'_p}}{\partial x^{a_p}}\Bigr)\,
      \Bigl(\frac{\partial x^{b_1}}{\partial x'^{\,j'_1}}\Bigr)\cdots
      \Bigl(\frac{\partial x^{b_q}}{\partial x'^{\,j'_q}}\Bigr)\,
      T^{\,a_1\cdots a_p}{}_{\,b_1\cdots b_q}\,.
   \]

2.  Purely covariant 5th-order tensor \(T_{pqrst}\) (\(p=0,q=5\))  
   \[
     T'_{\,i'j'k'l'm'}
     = 
     \frac{\partial x^{p}}{\partial x'^{\,i'}}
     \,\frac{\partial x^{q}}{\partial x'^{\,j'}}
     \,\frac{\partial x^{r}}{\partial x'^{\,k'}}
     \,\frac{\partial x^{s}}{\partial x'^{\,l'}}
     \,\frac{\partial x^{t}}{\partial x'^{\,m'}}
     \;T_{\,pqrst}\,.
   \]

3.  Purely contravariant 5th-order tensor \(T^{pqrst}\) (\(p=5,q=0\))  
   \[
     T'^{\,i'j'k'l'm'}
     =
     \frac{\partial x'^{\,i'}}{\partial x^{p}}
     \,\frac{\partial x'^{\,j'}}{\partial x^{q}}
     \,\frac{\partial x'^{\,k'}}{\partial x^{r}}
     \,\frac{\partial x'^{\,l'}}{\partial x^{s}}
     \,\frac{\partial x'^{\,m'}}{\partial x^{t}}
     \;T^{\,pqrst}\,.
   \]

Briefly, in matrix form (linear change of basis \(x'^{\,i}=A^{i}{}_{j}\,x^{j}\)):

– Covariant  
  \(\displaystyle 
    T'_{i'j'k'l'm'} 
    = A^{p}{}_{i'}\,A^{q}{}_{j'}\,A^{r}{}_{k'}\,A^{s}{}_{l'}\,A^{t}{}_{m'}\,
       T_{pq rst}.
  \)

– Contravariant  
  \(\displaystyle 
    T'^{i'j'k'l'm'} 
    = A^{\,i'}{}_{p}\,A^{\,j'}{}_{q}\,A^{\,k'}{}_{r}\,A^{\,l'}{}_{s}\,A^{\,m'}{}_{t}\,
       T^{pqrst}.
  \)

