2.  Compute the cockroach’s initial angular momentum about the axle:  
    \[
      L_{\rm bug,i}
      \;=\; m\,(R)\,v
      \;=\; (0.17)(0.15)(2.0)
      \;=\; 0.051\ {\rm kg\;m^2/s}.
    \]

3.  Compute the disk’s initial angular momentum:  
    \[
      L_{\rm disk,i}
      \;=\; I_{0}\,\omega_{0}
      \;=\; (5.0\times10^{-3})(-2.8)
      \;=\; -0.014\ {\rm kg\;m^2/s}.
    \]

4.  Total initial angular momentum:  
    \[
      L_{i}
      \;=\; L_{\rm disk,i}+L_{\rm bug,i}
      \;=\; -0.014 \;+\;0.051
      \;=\; 0.037\ {\rm kg\;m^2/s}.
    \]

5.  After the cockroach stops running, it sticks to the rim.  The final moment of inertia is  
    \[
      I_{f}
      \;=\; I_{0}+mR^{2}
      \;=\; 5.0\times10^{-3} \;+\;0.17\,(0.15)^{2}
      \;=\;8.825\times10^{-3}\ {\rm kg\;m^{2}}.
    \]

