Here is a step‐by‐step derivation, using an energy balance on a 1D slab element of cross‐sectional area \(A\) and thickness \(\d x\).  All equations in LaTeX.

1. Assumptions  
   • One‐dimensional conduction in the \(x\)–direction only  
   • Constant thermal conductivity \(k\)  
   • No internal heat generation (\(\dot q'''=0\))  
   • Material properties \(\rho\), \(c_p\) constant  

2. Energy balance on the element  
   Energy in by conduction at \(x\):  
   \[
     \dot Q_x \;=\;-\,k\,A\,\frac{\partial T}{\partial x}\Big|_{x}
   \]
   Energy out by conduction at \(x+\d x\):  
   \[
     \dot Q_{x+\d x}
     \;=\;
     -\,k\,A\,
     \frac{\partial T}{\partial x}\Big|_{x+\d x}
     \;\approx\;
     -\,k\,A\,
     \Bigl[\frac{\partial T}{\partial x} + \frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}\,\d x\Bigr]_{x}
   \]
   Net conduction in minus out:  
   \[
     \dot Q_{\text{in}}-\dot Q_{\text{out}}
     =
     \dot Q_x - \dot Q_{x+\d x}
     \;=\;
     -\,k\,A\,\frac{\partial T}{\partial x}
     \;-\;
     \bigl[-\,k\,A\bigl(\tfrac{\partial T}{\partial x}+ \tfrac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}\,\d x\bigr)\bigr]
     =
     k\,A\,\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}\,\d x
   \]
   No generation: \(\dot Q_{\rm gen}=0\).  
   Rate of increase of internal energy:  
   \[
     \dot Q_{\rm acc}
     =
     \rho\,c_p\,A\,\d x\;\frac{\partial T}{\partial t}
   \]
   Balance:  
   \[
     \dot Q_{\text{in}} - \dot Q_{\text{out}} + \dot Q_{\rm gen}
     = \dot Q_{\rm acc}
     \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
     k\,A\,\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}\,\d x
     =
     \rho\,c_p\,A\,\d x\;\frac{\partial T}{\partial t}
   \]

3. Divide by \(A\,\d x\) and simplify  
   \[
     k\,\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}
     =
     \rho\,c_p\;\frac{\partial T}{\partial t}
     \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
     \frac{\partial T}{\partial t}
     =
     \frac{k}{\rho\,c_p}\;\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}
     \;=\;
     \alpha\,\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}
   \]
   where \(\displaystyle\alpha\equiv\frac{k}{\rho\,c_p}\) is the thermal diffusivity.

Final Answers (brief)  
1. One‐dimensional transient heat conduction equation for a plane wall with constant \(k\) and no generation:  
   \[
     \boxed{
       \frac{\partial T}{\partial t}
       = \alpha\,\frac{\partial^2 T}{\partial x^2}
       \quad\text{with}\quad
       \alpha = \frac{k}{\rho\,c_p}
     }
   \]
2. Definitions:  
   • Thermal diffusivity \(\displaystyle\alpha = \frac{k}{\rho\,c_p}\)  
   • \(\rho\) = density, \(c_p\) = specific heat, \(k\) = thermal conductivity.

