Here is a step‐by‐step solution.  Since no numerical elevation difference was given between the reservoir surface A and the turbine inlet B, we shall carry the elevation drop as \(H_{z}=z_{A}-z_{B}\).  

1.  Continuity ⇒ velocity in pipe at B  
   \[
     Q = A\,V_B
     \quad\Longrightarrow\quad
     V_B = \frac{Q}{A}
           = \frac{Q}{\tfrac\pi4\,d^2}
     = \frac{0.6}{\tfrac\pi4(0.24)^2}
     \approx 13.26~\rm m/s
   \]

2.  Bernoulli (neglecting friction, same atmospheric press.) between free surface A (where \(V_A\approx0\)) and B:  
   \[
     z_A + \frac{V_A^2}{2g}
     = z_B + \frac{V_B^2}{2g}
     \;\Longrightarrow\;
     z_A - z_B
     = \frac{V_B^2}{2g}
     +\;H_{\rm useful}
   \]
   so the useful head available to the turbine is
   \[
     H_{\rm useful}
     = (z_A-z_B)\;-\;\frac{V_B^2}{2g}
     = H_{z}\;-\;\frac{(13.26)^2}{2\cdot9.81}
     = H_{z}\;-\;8.97~\rm m
   \]

3.  Power developed by the turbine (gross)  
   \[
     P_{\rm gross}
     = \rho\,g\,Q\,H_{\rm useful}
     = \rho\,g\,Q\Bigl(H_{z}-\frac{V_B^2}{2g}\Bigr)
   \]
   and the net output at \(\eta=85\%\) is
   \[
     P_{\rm out}
     = \eta\,P_{\rm gross}
     = 0.85\;\rho\,g\,Q
       \Bigl(H_{z}-8.97\Bigr)
   \]
   with \(\rho=1000\rm\;kg/m^3,\;g=9.81\;m/s^2\).  

Final formula for the turbine output power:  
\[
  \boxed{
    P_{\rm out}
    =0.85\,(1000)(9.81)(0.6)
    \Bigl(H_{z}-8.97\Bigr)
