Here is the step‐by‐step solution.  In what follows,  
Rcoil=1.5 cm=0.015 m,  N=10,  Icoil=2.5 A;  
aloop=1.0 mm=1.0×10⁻³ m,  Rloop=2.0×10⁻⁴ Ω;  
v=75 m/s,  t=0.200 s ⇒ z=v t=15.0 m.  

1) On‐axis field of the N‐turn coil at distance z:  
\[
B(z)\;=\;\frac{\mu_0\,N\,I_{\rm coil}\,R_{\rm coil}^2}
              {2\,(R_{\rm coil}^2+z^2)^{3/2}}.
\]

2) Magnetic flux through the small loop (single turn):  
\[
\Phi(z)\;=\;B(z)\,\pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2.
\]

3) Induced emf by motion along z:  
\[
\mathcal{E}
=-\frac{d\Phi}{dt}
=-\pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2\;\frac{dB}{dz}\;\frac{dz}{dt}
=-\pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2\,v\;\frac{d}{dz}
   \Big[\frac{\mu_0\,N\,I_{\rm coil}\,R_{\rm coil}^2}
             {2\,(R_{\rm coil}^2+z^2)^{3/2}}\Big].
\]
Since 
\(\displaystyle\frac{d}{dz}\frac1{(R^2+z^2)^{3/2}}
=-\frac{3z}{(R^2+z^2)^{5/2}}\),
one finds
\[
\mathcal{E}
=\;-\pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2\,v\;
\frac{\mu_0 N I_{\rm coil}R_{\rm coil}^2}{2}
\;\Big(-\frac{3z}{(R_{\rm coil}^2+z^2)^{5/2}}\Big)
\;=\;\frac{3\mu_0\,N\,I_{\rm coil}\,R_{\rm coil}^2\,
             \pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2\,v\,z}
            {2\,(R_{\rm coil}^2+z^2)^{5/2}}.
\]

4) Induced current (Ohm’s law):  
\[
I_{\rm ind}
=\frac{|\mathcal{E}|}{R_{\rm loop}}
=\frac{3\,\mu_0\,N\,I_{\rm coil}\,R_{\rm coil}^2\,
         \pi\,a_{\rm loop}^2\,v\,z}
       {2\,R_{\rm loop}\,(R_{\rm coil}^2+z^2)^{5/2}}.
\]

5) Numerical evaluation at z=15 m:  
\[
I_{\rm ind}\approx2.5\times10^{-13}\;{\rm A}.
\]
Direction: as the loop moves away the flux ↓, so the induced field must point in the original +z‐direction.  Hence the induced current is counterclockwise as seen from +z.  

Final answer (brief):  
I_{\rm ind}=2.5×10⁻¹³ A (ccw as viewed from +z).

