   \[
     v_{\rm rms}
     = \sqrt{\frac{1}{N}\sum_{i=1}^{N}v_i^2}
     = \sqrt{\frac{4v_1^2 + 2v_2^2 + 4v_3^2}{10}}
     = \sqrt{\frac{4\cdot200^2 + 2\cdot500^2 + 4\cdot600^2}{10}}
     = \sqrt{\frac{2100000}{10}}
     = \sqrt{210000}
     \approx 458.3\ {\rm m/s}.
   \]

4. Comparison  
   Since the speeds are not all equal,  
   \[
     v_{\rm rms} \;>\; v_{\rm avg}
     \quad\Bigl(458.3\!>\!420\Bigr).
   \]

Final answers (brief):  
a) 420 m/s  
b) 458.3 m/s  
c) Yes, \(v_{\rm rms}>v_{\rm avg}\).

